                <listApp><app><note>Text after ILTermini with changes based on the autopsy</note></app></listApp>
                <app loc="3"><note>Bivona (1994) reads s(uo) at the end of line three. This is not evident on autopsy, but would complete the formula.</note></app>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>[...] To [...] Lesbius, freedman of Publius [...], [and] [...] Damophilus, freedman of [...], [?] made [this] from his own resources.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" resp="#AA">
                <p>It is clear that lines 1-2 address the dedicatees, both freedmen, but that line 3 would have included the name of the dedicant. The cognomen Lesbius, of Greek origin, is common. The cognomen Damophilus, also of Greek origin, is less common but nonetheless elsewhere attested in the empire.</p>
            </div>
